(1)
k!e
 \sum_{n=0}^k \frac{k!}{(k-n)!}=k!\sum_{n=0}^k \frac{1}{(k-n)!}. 
 k!\sum_{m=0}^k \frac{1}{m!}. \tag{1} 
 k!\sum_{m=0}^\infty \frac{1}{m!} = k!e, 
 k! \sum_{m=k+1}^\infty \frac{1}{m!} = \frac{1}{k+1}+\frac{1}{(k+1)(k+2)}+\cdots. 
 \sum_{m=1}^\infty \frac{1}{(k+1)^m} = \frac1k < \frac12. 
